@124191 = ~Secret Word~
//
@12419 = ~Secret Word
Level: 4
School: Enchantment
Range: Long
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: vs. Spells

When a Secret Word spell is uttered, it will dispel two layers of spell protections on the target. Thus, it will remove a Spell Deflection and a Minor Spell Deflection, or a Minor Spell Protection and a Globe of Invulnerability, et cetera. This will always dispel the highest-level spell protection on the target (affecting up to 7th-level protection spells). Magic resistance does not affect this spell.

Additionally, a Secret Word has an "ear worm" quality which can unbalance the target and make spellcasting difficult. This is similar to the effect of Deafness, imposing a 50% chance of casting failure for one round on a failed save vs. spells. This effect can occur regardless of any spell deflections or level-based immunity the target may have.

The spell protections dispelled by Secret Word include: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Deflection, Globe of Invulnerability, and Greater Spell Deflection.

Secret Word will not dispel any spell protections on a target protected by Spell Trap or Shield of the Archons. A Spell Shield will block Secret Word from dispelling any protections, though the Spell Shield itself will be fully consumed in the effort.
~
