@126081 = ~Pierce Magic~
//
@12608 = ~Pierce Magic
Level: 6
School: Abjuration
Range: Long
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast upon a target creature there will be three effects. First, the target's Magic Resistance, if any, will be nullified and set to zero for two rounds. This occurs regardless of any spell deflections or level-based immunity the target may have.

Second, this spell will destroy a Spell Shield protecting the target.

Third, this spell will dispel two layers of spell protections from the creature, similar to Secret Word. Thus, it will dispel Greater Spell Deflection and Spell Deflection; or Spell Deflection and Globe of Invulnerability; et cetera. This will always dispel the highest-level spell protections on the target (affecting up to 7th-level protection spells). Magic resistance does not affect this spell.

The spell protections dispelled by Pierce Magic include: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Deflection, Globe of Invulnerability, Greater Spell Deflection, and Shield of the Archons. 

The effects of Pierce Magic are not deterred by a Spell Shield. Pierce Magic will not dispel any spell protections on a target protected by Spell Trap.
~
