@127041 = ~Ruby Ray of Reversal~
//
@12704 = ~Ruby Ray of Reversal
Level: 7
School: Alteration
Range: Long
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: vs. Spells

When a Ruby Ray of Reversal is directed at a target, it will dispel three layers of spell protections on the target. Thus, it will dispel Greater Spell Deflection, Spell Deflection, and Minor Spell Deflection; or Greater Spell Deflection, Spell Deflection, and Globe of Invulnerability; et cetera. This will always dispel the highest-level spell protection on the target. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.

Additionally, A Ruby Ray is capable of destroying a Spell Trap, the most powerful spell protection. In this case, the Ruby Ray is consumed and will not remove any lesser spell protections.

Finally, the searing light of the Ruby Ray can blind the target for one round, and this effect can occur regardless of any spell protections the target may have. A successful saving throw vs. spells at a -2 penalty will negate this effect.

The spell protections dispelled by Ruby Ray of Reversal include: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Deflection, Globe of Invulnerability, Greater Spell Deflection, Shield of the Archons, and Spell Trap.

A Spell Shield will block Ruby Ray of Reversal from dispelling any protections, though the Spell Shield itself will be fully consumed in the effort.
~
