School: Abjuration
Range: Personal
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

This immensely powerful abjuration combines two capabilities. First, it acts as a spell protection, allowing the caster to ignore the effects of *any* spells cast at or near <PRO_HIMHER>. In this regard it could be considered a one-way Anti-Magic Shell, or a supreme version of a Globe of Invulnerability, blocking all spell effects of levels one through nine. Second, the Spell Trap acts like a powerful Spell Shield, blocking magic attacks such as Spell Thrust or Pierce Magic from dispelling any of the caster's lesser spell protections. A Spell trap must be removed by a Ruby Ray of Reversal or Pierce Shield spell before enemies can begin to remove other, lesser protections such as Spell Deflections.
~
